Re: How To Properly Hand Write In Japanese
by yangmuye » Wed 09.29.2010 9:06 am If you want to be a calligrapher, you may learn how to write "cursive" kanji. They may write them instead of kana.Otherwise, you'd better don't add some "extra strokes" by yourself. Just follow a textbook's suggestion.
yangmuye
