Re: How To Properly Hand Write In Japanese
by Snowflake » Thu 09.30.2010 8:03 am Good morning, Jerrid! I did a little search for you here on TJP and found this Kanji Handwriting Thread. It's from a few years ago; the last entry was made in Sept 2009. There are 20 pages, many of which include images of our own forum members' handwriting! Perhaps taking a peek at other people's real handwriting will give you more confidence in your own.From what I see in that thread, it looks as if there is a big variety in handwriting and, provided it's neat, well-spaced and legible, it's acceptable. I hope this helps!
