Re: How To Properly Hand Write In Japanese
by Hyperworm » Fri 10.29.2010 9:15 am Wow. That's really misleading.The stroke order diagrams in the katakana pages are using a font set to italics.So normally vertical strokes tend left at the bottom.The version you see in the kana chart at the top of that page, and just to the right of "Sound", is the correct one. ._.(キ's vertical stroke should tend right a little bit at the bottom.)
